name: HttpRequest
description: Use the HttpRequest class to programmatically create HTTP requests like GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE.

getbody().name: getBody
getbody().description: Retrieves the body of this request.

getbodyasblob().name: getBodyAsBlob
getbodyasblob().description: Retrieves the body of this request as a Blob.

getbodydocument().name: getBodyDocument
getbodydocument().description: Retrieves the body of this request as a DOM document.

getcompressed().name: getCompressed
getcompressed().description: If true, the request body is compressed, false otherwise.

getendpoint().name: getEndpoint
getendpoint().description: Retrieves the URL for the endpoint of the external server for this request.

getheader(string).name: getHeader
getheader(string).description: Retrieves the contents of the request header.

getmethod().name: getMethod
getmethod().description: Returns the type of method used by HttpRequest.

setbody(string).name: setBody
setbody(string).description: Sets the contents of the body for this request.

setbodyasblob(blob).name: setBodyAsBlob
setbodyasblob(blob).description: Sets the contents of the body for this request using a Blob.

setbodydocument(dom.document).name: setBodyDocument
setbodydocument(dom.document).description: Sets the contents of the body for this request. The contents represent a DOM document.

setclientcertificate(string,string).name: setClientCertificate
setclientcertificate(string,string).signature: public Void setClientCertificate(String clientCert, String password)
setclientcertificate(string,string).overrideSignature: public override Void setClientCertificate(String clientCert, String password)
setclientcertificate(string,string).description: This method is deprecated. Use setClientCertificateName instead.

setclientcertificatename(string).name: setClientCertificateName
setclientcertificatename(string).description: If the external service requires a client certificate for authentication, set the certificate name.

setcompressed(boolean).name: setCompressed
setcompressed(boolean).description: If true, the data in the body is delivered to the endpoint in the gzip compressed format. If false, no compression format is used.

setendpoint(string).name: setEndpoint
setendpoint(string).description: Specifies the endpoint for this request.

endpoint.name: endpoint
endpoint.description: Possible values for the endpoint: Endpoint URLhttps://my_endpoint.example.com/some_path   Named credential URL, which contains the scheme callout, the name of the named credential, and, optionally, an appended pathcallout:My_Named_Credential/some_path

setheader(string,string).name: setHeader
setheader(string,string).signature: public Void setHeader(String key, String value)
setheader(string,string).overrideSignature: public override Void setHeader(String key, String value)
setheader(string,string).description: Sets the contents of the request header.

setmethod(string).name: setMethod
setmethod(string).description: Sets the type of method to be used for the HTTP request.

method.name: method
method.description: Possible values for the method type include: DELETE  GET  HEAD  POST  PUT  TRACE

settimeout(integer).name: setTimeout
settimeout(integer).description: Sets the timeout in milliseconds for the request.

tostring().name: toString
tostring().description: Returns a string containing the URL for the endpoint of the external server for this request and the method used, for example, Endpoint=http://YourServer, Method=POST

httprequest().name: HttpRequest
httprequest().description: Creates a new instance of the HttpRequest class.
